            "content": "<p>I&#39;ve ranted about the risks of over-investment in CCS (Carbon Capture and Storage) for years, the moral hazard it invites - especially as a license to pollute. Turns out oil companies have been playing the public all along, talking it up as a solution while quietly distancing themselves from it as a technology not near practically viable:</p><p><a href=\"https://www.vox.com/climate/363076/climate-change-solution-shell-exxon-mobil-carbon-capture\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\" translate=\"no\"><span class=\"invisible\">https://www.</span><span class=\"ellipsis\">vox.com/climate/363076/climate</span><span class=\"invisible\">-change-solution-shell-exxon-mobil-carbon-capture</span></a> </p><p>(via <span class=\"h-card\" translate=\"no\"><a href=\"https://collapsible.systems/@Christina\" class=\"u-url mention\">@<span>Christina</span></a></span> )</p><p><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/climate\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>climate</span></a> <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/pollution\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>pollution</span></a></p>",
